 {"id":"mu-d033","title":"/handoff event + session-resume-from-event: cache-managed mid-session continuation","description":"## Idea (operator 2026-05-17)\n\nAdd a /handoff command (or prompt+tool exchange producing a Handoff event) that:\n\n1. Captures a handoff message into the session event log — the message itself contains whatever state the next session needs (pointers to information to reuse, summary, current goal, etc.)\n2. On restart of a session, the new instance can be pointed at that event and pick up cleanly without re-processing the whole prior context\n3. Primary motivation is cache management — handoff is usually done because the prompt cache has gotten unwieldy or stale, so we want to checkpoint-then-restart with a smaller hot context\n\n## Why this fits mu's architecture\n\n- The event log is already the substrate (per specs/architecture/event-sourced-context.md). A Handoff event is just another EventPayload variant — or even just a specially-tagged assistant_message_event with content acting as the handoff payload.\n- 'Session resume from event' is the projection: rebuild context from {SessionCreated → Handoff} rather than {SessionCreated → all_subsequent_events}.\n- It's the mid-session analog of mu-mh4 'sessions persist across daemon restart' — same machinery, narrower scope (intra-day, intra-task), different motivation (cache reset vs daemon restart).\n\n## Design questions\n\n- **Event shape**: dedicated EventPayload::Handoff { summary, pointers: Vec<EventPointer>, goal: Option<String> } vs reuse assistant_message_event with a structural marker? The pointer-set framing (skill.rs:'activating a skill IS pointer-set membership') suggests the dedicated variant is cleaner.\n- **Resume protocol**: new RPC session.resume_from_handoff { session_id, event_id }? Or session.create with optional 'resume_anchor: EventPointer'?\n- **Cache implication**: the resume should produce a SMALLER prompt than the original context (that's the whole point). Provider-side caching invalidation is implicit — different prompt = different cache entry. Worth confirming the Anthropic provider clears its cache_breakpoints accordingly.\n\n## Composes with\n\n- mu-mh4 territory (persist sessions across daemon restart) — both depend on event-log-as-source-of-truth.\n- /compaction (mu-kgu) — adjacent: compaction shrinks the rope in place; handoff is a structural restart that drops everything except the explicit handoff message. Operator may want both available, used for different reasons.\n- Mailbox / cross-session pointers — a handoff message in session A could point at events in session B.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- /handoff command (or equivalent) writes a structured event to the session log\n- Resume mechanism reads that event and starts a new session with content seeded from the handoff\n- Verifiable cache benefit on resume (next assistant turn shows cache_creation_input_tokens >> cache_read_input_tokens, i.e. fresh cache, not stale-prefix-reuse)\n\n## Source\n\nOperator message 2026-05-17 during opus-review session.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-05-17T19:41:37.065050927Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-05-17T19:41:37.065050927Z","source_repo":"mu","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","cache","event-log","handoff","sessions"]}
 {"id":"mu-d04a","title":"mu-solo: live-viewport streaming + nested collapsible concurrent turns (demux by session_id, commit-on-finalize)","description":"## Problem\n\nmu-solo commits streaming text to linear terminal scrollback incrementally (`vp.insert_before` per delta; `streaming_chars_emitted` tracks how much is committed). Scrollback is append-only, so two concurrent streams (main turn + `/btw` sidecar) cannot interleave coherently — which is why `/btw` is guarded during streaming (app.rs ~753/799/982). The single streaming state (`streaming_text` / `streaming_header_open` / `streaming_chars_emitted` / `pending_close` / `streaming_route`) assumes exactly one in-flight turn.\n\nThe same incremental-commit model is the root of two open bugs:\n- mu-304g: F3 inline render stalls ~20 lines into a streaming response.\n- mu-926g: empty/unclosed assistant header artifacts in agent loops.\n\n## Design (converged with operator, 2026-05-28)\n\nENGINE — live region, commit-on-finalize. Render in-flight turn(s) in a live, mutable viewport region (the `DynamicViewport` already manages a dynamic bottom area for the grow-up prompt) redrawn each tick from per-session buffers, and `insert_before` a block into scrollback only on `assistant_text_finalized`, then drop it from the live set. A live region redraws from scratch each frame, so N blocks can grow at once with no interleave problem. Commit blocks ordered by START timestamp so out-of-order finishes still read chronologically.\n\nDEMUX by session_id. `handle_notification` (~app.rs:1904) already resolves each delta's session_id to main-vs-sidecar; route deltas into per-session StreamState (replace the single streaming_* fields). Then relax the /btw guard so it fires mid-stream.\n\nLAYOUT — inline collapsible child events. Render a /btw as a timestamp-anchored, collapsible CHILD event inside the outer assistant block, generalizing the existing inline tool-call rendering (emit_tool_call_started/completed) so a model tool-call and a /btw aside become two flavors of one inline-collapsible-child-event model. Collapsed = +you / +assistant one-liners; expand to read. Preserves causal flow (you see where in the turn you stepped out).\n\nLABELS as provenance (folds mu-za0u; roadmap #2). Replace the bare `assistant` label with session:provider:model (alias-able per mu-za0u; daemon hoisted to the status line via the shipped MCP status-line rail; full daemon:session:provider:model recoverable on expand / /status). The label IS the honesty layer: a /btw farmed to a different session/provider:model wears its origin (opus main + haiku aside reads truthfully). NOTE: a /btw is NOT the main model's tool call — it is an operator aside to the sidecar session, represented as a labeled operator digression, not a model tool_use.\n\nCOLLAPSE/EXPAND. ratatui in-pane overlay (Clear + bordered Block) for expand; same affordance serves long tool output (the Claude Code ctrl+o pattern). No external multiplexer needed.\n\n## Phases\n\n1. Engine: per-session StreamState + live-viewport rendering of in-flight turn(s); commit-on-finalize; timestamp-ordered commit. (Incidentally fixes mu-304g / mu-926g.)\n2. Demux + unguard: route deltas by session_id; relax the /btw streaming guard.\n3. Nested layout: inline collapsible timestamp-anchored child events; unify tool-calls + /btw.\n4. Provenance labels (mu-za0u / #2): session:provider:model alias; daemon to status line.\n5. Collapse/expand: ratatui overlay; reused for long tool output.\n\n## Folds in / relates\n- mu-304g (streaming stall ~20 lines) — fixed by Phase 1.\n- mu-926g (empty/unclosed assistant header) — fixed by Phase 1.\n- mu-za0u (model attribution / interleaved view) — implemented by Phase 4.\n\n## Constraints\n- mu-solo is single-pane by design (deliberate pivot off mu-tui's Inline/Fullscreen state machine; memory e16c24a6). This work stays in-pane (ratatui overlays). True separate panes = mu-6nuq, deferred.\n\n## Provenance\nDesign converged in a mu-solo planning session 2026-05-28 (operator + claude). Covers roadmap items #1 (/btw runs during streaming) + #2 (model-attribution labels). The /btw fix had no prior bead; see memory 521c83c2 followup #2.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-05-28T20:10:02.776946422Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-07T03:02:59.990904997Z","source_repo":"mu","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["mu-solo","streaming","tui"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mu-d04a","depends_on_id":"mu-33o1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-31T19:06:16.055085600Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"mu-d04a","depends_on_id":"mu-hsyt","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-31T19:06:15.786722130Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"mu-d04a","depends_on_id":"mu-jnbh","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-31T19:06:15.919992965Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"mu-d04a","depends_on_id":"mu-mlcg","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-31T18:01:16.099194345Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"mu-d04a","depends_on_id":"mu-p5pd","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-31T19:06:16.193862315Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":64,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"tcovert","text":"PHASE 1 SCOPE DECISION (2026-05-28): go 'foundation', not the line-patch. Build the structured turn model + composable renderers now — it's what Phase 3 (nested collapsible /btw) requires anyway, so patching first then tearing out is the throwaway path.\n\nCURRENT STATE (terrain): mu-solo has NO model/view split. It's immediate-mode imperative — a notification arrives, an emit_* fn builds Vec<Line> AND draws the box AND insert_before's it to scrollback in one step, then forgets it. No retained model, no component tree. Streaming text commits incrementally (emit_streaming -> emit_body_chunk per newline) = the mu-304g/926g cause.\n\nDESIGN (immediate-mode; NO retained view objects / offsets / observer-command machinery — re-render the model each frame, ratatui paints):\n- MODEL on App: in-flight Turn { route: TurnRoute, items: Vec<TurnItem> }. enum TurnItem = Text(String) | ToolCall{name,primary_arg} | ToolResult{outcome} (+ later Btw(Turn) for Phase 3 nesting). Phase 1: one in-flight turn; Phase 2 makes it a per-session map keyed by session_id.\n- VIEW: pure composable fns in render.rs — render_turn(&Turn, wrap_width, max_rows)->Vec<Line> delegating to render_text_item / render_tool_call / render_tool_result. Extract today's emit_* / emit_body_chunk / block_lines line-building into these pure fns. Tail-truncate to max_rows for the live (in-flight) preview; emit closer only when committing.\n- LIVE: render_viewport renders the in-flight Turn into the viewport above the prompt each frame (tail-truncated, no closer). focus_mode suppresses the preview (model still built + committed).\n- handle_notification builds the MODEL: text_delta extends the trailing Text item; tool_call_started pushes ToolCall; tool_call_completed pushes ToolResult; assistant_text_finalized = segment marker; done/error -> render Turn with closer, insert_before to scrollback, drop the model.\n- DELETE the incremental path (emit_streaming + immediate insert_before inside emit_tool_call_*; the logic moves into the pure item renderers). streaming_chars_emitted/pending_close/streaming_header_open retire in favor of model+render.\n\nFIXES: mu-304g (no incremental scrollback commit -> no stall) + mu-926g (no eager empty header). SETS UP: Phase 2 (per-session map + demux + unguard /btw) and Phase 3 (Btw(Turn) item + collapse/expand). Execution is a clean focused run against this spec.","created_at":"2026-05-28T20:37:08Z"},{"id":65,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"tcovert","text":"Phase 1 progress (2026-05-28, claude-personal): foundation LANDED + verified green; daily-driver path untouched.\n\nDONE (additive, zero-risk):\n- render.rs: pure renderers render_turn / render_turn_item / render_tool_result / turn_closer / tail_truncate + TurnItem enum {Text, ToolCall{display_name,primary_arg}, ToolResult{kind,text}, Error}. Reproduce the existing visual contract (header / | body / bullet ToolName(arg) yellow-bold / |   bounded preview / red error / closer). 11 render:: tests pass incl. the codex-validated invariant 'tail_truncate(full) == tail of full render' (structural guard vs mu-304g).\n- app.rs: Turn{route,items} + Turn::{new,push_text,has_output} + App.live_turn: Option<Turn> + ctor init. Builds green (expected dead_code warns until wired).\n\nPRIOR ART: studied codex-rs/tui (now indexed). Confirms architecture (HistoryCell model + StreamController live region + insert_history commit). Keep ENUM TurnItem (codex trait only because ~12 cell types); keep Phase-1 commit-whole-turn-on-done (codex on_commit_tick = future opt, separate bead not P1).\n\nREMAINING WIRING (daily-driver-mutating; do atomically + visual-verify in one run):\n1. handle_notification -> build live_turn (text_delta->push_text; tool started/completed->push items, move titlecase_tool/extract_primary_arg to build-time; finalized->replace trailing Text per mu-wk2; done/error->render_turn+turn_closer, insert_before, drop live_turn).\n2. render_viewport: render live_turn above separator each frame, tail-truncated; focus_mode suppresses preview (model still built+committed).\n3. DELETE emit_streaming/emit_body_chunk/flush_streaming_close/ensure_streaming_header_open + streaming_text/header_open/chars_emitted/pending_close fields; fix cmd_btw guard (live_turn.is_some()) + handle_message phase-2 closer.\n4. build+clippy+test; hand to thaddeus_user for visual check. Fixes mu-304g + mu-926g by construction.","created_at":"2026-05-28T21:36:36Z"},{"id":66,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"tcovert","text":"Phase 1 IMPLEMENTED + verified green (2026-05-28, claude-personal). Wiring complete, daily-driver path swapped to the structured model.\n\nDONE:\n- handle_notification builds the model: text_delta -> Turn::push_text (extends trailing Text item, new item after a tool call); assistant_text_finalized -> replace trailing Text with canonical (mu-wk2); tool_call_started -> push ToolCall (titlecase_tool/extract_primary_arg moved to build-time); tool_call_completed -> push ToolResult{kind,text}; done/error -> render_turn + turn_closer, insert_before to scrollback, drop live_turn (error attaches as trailing Error item; empty/no-turn -> standalone no-output/error block).\n- render_viewport renders live_turn above the prompt each frame, tail-truncated to a budget that guarantees >=1 (up to 3) prompt rows stay visible; focus_mode suppresses the preview (model still built+committed).\n- DELETED emit_streaming / emit_body_chunk / flush_streaming_close / ensure_streaming_header_open + fields streaming_text/streaming_header_open/streaming_chars_emitted/pending_close/ask_had_output/pending_skip_assistant (last was write-only dead code). Kept streaming_route (synced w/ live_turn.route; used by /cancel). Guards (Ctrl-C cancel, /btw, /skill) now check live_turn.is_some().\n- net diff crates/mu-solo: +500/-495. cargo build + clippy clean; 32 mu-solo tests pass (incl render:: tail-invariant). Fixes mu-304g (no incremental scrollback commit -> no stall) + mu-926g (no eager empty header) by construction.\n\nPENDING: operator visual TUI check in thaddeus_user workspace (live gpt-5.5 session). Uncommitted on disk (beads-ride). Phases 2-5 (per-session demux + /btw unguard, nested collapsible child events, provenance labels, collapse/expand overlay) remain.","created_at":"2026-05-28T21:54:01Z"},{"id":67,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"tcovert","text":"PHASE 2 SPEC — per-session demux + /btw unguard (2026-05-28, claude-personal, written warm right after Phase 1 shipped to main @ 9de8e4c3).\n\nGOAL: let a /btw sidecar turn stream CONCURRENTLY with the main turn. Phase 1 built the substrate (structured Turn, live-region render, commit-on-done); Phase 2 generalizes the single in-flight turn to a per-session set and drops the guard that blocks /btw mid-stream.\n\n== CURRENT STATE (post-Phase-1, crates/mu-solo/src/app.rs) ==\n- Model: `App.live_turn: Option<Turn>` (single in-flight turn). `Turn { route: TurnRoute, items: Vec<render::TurnItem> }` + Turn::{new(route), push_text(delta), has_output()}. TurnRoute = Main | Btw (header_label/color/you_label/you_color).\n- `streaming_route: Option<TurnRoute>` — single global, kept in sync with the live turn; used by cmd_cancel + as the route fallback in handlers.\n- handle_notification: top resolves `let sid = params[\"session_id\"]` and classifies main (== self.session_id) / sidecar (== self.sidecar_session_id) / unknown (drops with return). Arms: text_delta -> live_turn.get_or_insert_with(|| Turn::new(route)).push_text; assistant_text_finalized -> replace trailing Text item (mu-wk2); tool_call_started -> push TurnItem::ToolCall{display_name,primary_arg} (titlecase_tool/extract_primary_arg at build time); tool_call_completed -> push TurnItem::ToolResult{kind,text}; done|error -> `self.live_turn.take()`, commit (render::render_turn + render::turn_closer, insert_before) or standalone no-output/error block, then `streaming_route = None`.\n- render_viewport (~line 583): builds `preview` from `self.live_turn.as_ref()` (skipped if focus_mode), tail-truncated to budget = MAX_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT - (4 + menu_rows + prompt_lines.min(3)); prepended to `lines` above the separator. VIEWPORT_HEIGHT=5, MAX_VIEWPORT_HEIGHT=20.\n- Guards keyed off `live_turn.is_some()`: Ctrl-C cancel (key handler), cmd_btw (\"wait — main turn still streaming\"), cmd_skill (\"wait — turn still streaming\").\n- fire_ask: streaming_route=Main, live_turn=Some(Turn::new(Main)). cmd_btw: after sidecar creation, streaming_route=Btw, live_turn=Some(Turn::new(Btw)). cmd_cancel: matches streaming_route to pick session to cancel.\n- render.rs renderers are already multi-turn-ready (render_turn takes label+color+items; pure). render:: tests = 11; total mu-solo tests = 32.\n\n== PHASE 2 CHANGES ==\n1. MODEL: replace `live_turn: Option<Turn>` with an ordered per-session map. RECOMMEND `live_turns: Vec<Turn>` with a new `session_id: String` field on Turn (avoids adding the indexmap dep; ≤2 concurrent turns so linear scan by sid is trivial; Vec order = start order = stable render/commit order). Helper: `fn live_turn_mut(&mut self, sid: &str) -> &mut Turn` that finds-or-creates (push) the turn for sid. Turn::new becomes `Turn::new(session_id, route)`.\n\n2. ROUTE FROM SID, not the global streaming_route. Add `fn route_for_sid(&self, sid: &str) -> TurnRoute` (sid==self.session_id -> Main; sid==sidecar -> Btw). Every handler arm uses sid (already in scope at top of handle_notification) to get/create the right turn and its route. This removes the ambiguity the single streaming_route can't handle with two concurrent turns.\n\n3. handle_notification arms: text_delta/finalized/tool_started/tool_completed -> operate on `self.live_turn_mut(sid)` instead of the single field. done|error -> remove + commit the turn for THIS sid only (find index by sid, remove, commit it); leave other in-flight turns alone. (sid is \"\" for some session-less notifications — keep the existing drop/Main-fallback behavior; don't create empty turns from provider_status.)\n\n4. RELAX /btw GUARD: delete the `if self.live_turn.is_some()` block in cmd_btw so a sidecar turn can start mid-main-stream. cmd_btw creates the Btw turn keyed by the sidecar session_id. KEEP the magenta \"assistant ⋅ btw\" / \"you ⋅ btw\" labels — that route-colored framing is the visual separation between the two concurrent streams (no mux/panes; mu-6nuq deferred).\n\n5. OTHER GUARDS: Ctrl-C and cmd_skill currently check live_turn.is_some() -> change to `!self.live_turns.is_empty()`. DECISION NEEDED: should /skill stay blocked while ANY turn streams? /skill injects context into a NEW main ask, which collides with an in-flight MAIN turn — recommend: /skill blocked only if a MAIN turn is in flight (not merely a btw sidecar). cmd_btw should NOT be blocked by an in-flight btw — but DO guard against a second concurrent btw if the sidecar is single (one btw at a time): block if a Btw turn is already live.\n\n6. render_viewport: render EACH in-flight turn (Vec order = start order), each as its own open block (render_turn, no closer), route-colored. For ≤2 turns, concatenate all turn renders then tail_truncate the combined block to the same budget (simplest; acceptable that the top turn's header can scroll off under heavy load). If you want both headers always visible, split the budget per turn instead — note the trade-off. focus_mode still suppresses ALL previews.\n\n7. streaming_route FATE: with route now derived per-sid, the single streaming_route is redundant for routing. cmd_cancel still needs a target: DECISION — cancel the MAIN turn by default (most intuitive), or cancel all in-flight. Recommend: /cancel cancels the main session's turn if one is live, else the btw. Either remove streaming_route and derive, or keep it only as \"primary turn route\" for /cancel. Don't leave it half-wired.\n\n== WATCH-FORS / RISKS ==\n- Commit ordering: if btw finishes before main, btw's block lands in scrollback ABOVE the still-streaming main (finish-order, not start-order). That's acceptable and chronological-by-finish; the original design note about \"start-timestamp order\" refers to LIVE render order (keep main above btw consistently), not scrollback. Don't try to reorder committed scrollback.\n- Don't spuriously create empty turns for session-less / provider_status events. Only create on first content event (delta/tool).\n- Empty-turn-on-done per session: keep the \"(turn ended, no output)\" / error path, scoped to the finishing sid.\n- /cancel ambiguity (see #7). Ctrl-C cancel likewise needs a target policy.\n- sidecar_session_id is created lazily in cmd_btw; ensure route_for_sid handles the sid before/after creation.\n\n== VERIFY ==\n- cargo build -p mu-solo && cargo clippy -p mu-solo && cargo test -p mu-solo (extend render tests for 2 concurrent turns; keep the tail-invariant per turn).\n- Visual (thaddeus_user, live gpt-5.5): start a main turn, fire /btw mid-stream, confirm BOTH stream live (white main block + magenta btw block) and each commits to scrollback on its own done. Confirm /cancel + Ctrl-C target sanely. Then describe the change + advance main (direct push, branch-protection bypass — proper PR is a future cleanup).\n\nFoundation for Phase 3 (nested collapsible child events) is unaffected by these changes.","created_at":"2026-05-28T22:57:04Z"},{"id":92,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"claude","text":"DECOMPOSITION (mu-mlcg, 2026-05-31). Terrain-checked the current mu-solo against the 5-phase design (the 2026-05-28 design notes predate the code).\n\nPhase 1 (structured Turn/TurnItem model + pure renderers in render.rs + commit-on-finalize): ALREADY DONE on main — Turn{route,items} (app.rs:121-159), enum TurnItem (render.rs:124-138), render_turn/render_turn_item/render_tool_result + 9 tests, commit-on-finalize via insert_before only on done/error (app.rs:2028-2103); the old incremental fields (streaming_text/header_open/chars_emitted/pending_close) are gone. render.rs:109-119 documents this fixes mu-304g + mu-926g — so those two bugs do NOT manifest in mu-solo (operator: close them if mu-tui's F3 path is considered superseded by mu-solo; left open since they were filed against mu-tui).\n\nRemaining work, filed as right-sized sub-beads (shared contract = the Turn model, already landed, so these build on it):\n- mu-hsyt — Phase 2: per-session Turn map + concurrent /btw streaming (demux already routes by session_id; in-flight state is still a single Option<TurnRoute>, /btw still guarded). blockedBy: none.\n- mu-jnbh — Phase 3: nested collapsible child events (Btw/tool-call as inline child). blockedBy mu-hsyt.\n- mu-33o1 — Phase 4: provenance labels (session:provider:model; folds mu-za0u). Independent (self-contained header change).\n- mu-p5pd — Phase 5: collapse/expand ratatui overlay (children + long tool output). blockedBy mu-jnbh.\n\nEach is one-module-ish, independently testable, ~1-2h. mu-d04a now blockedBy all four (it's the umbrella). Related bug mu-wf5w (missing done-terminus) is a distinct daemon/finalize race — linked, not folded.","created_at":"2026-05-31T19:06:38Z"},{"id":185,"issue_id":"mu-d04a","author":"tcovert","text":"OPERATOR REQUIREMENTS (dictated 2026-06-06 evening; supersede any implied design doctrine — explicitly 'no doctrine, not sure it works' re both the parked buffered impl urmmluyq AND the concurrent spec in mu-hsyt; requirements over implementation):\n\nTHE FAILURE BEING SOLVED: operator sends a refinement ('you don't need to worry about X') WHILE the model is processing the previous message. Wire ordering delivers it after the response, so the model misreads concurrent steering as a post-hoc verdict and redoes work that already accounted for it. The damage is stale-correction over-reaction, not ordering.\n\nR1 — dispatch order is inviolate. A message precedes the provider calls it feeds. Never re-insert a mid-stream message before the response it didn't feed: temporally correct, causally a lie.\n\nR2 — both truths persist. The event log records arrival time (already does). Projections must preserve BOTH where the message sat in time AND which provider calls it did/didn't feed. Two questions, two honest answers.\n\nR3 — concurrency annotated in-band. When assembling the next provider call, a message that arrived mid-generation is marked 'authored while the previous response was streaming — author had not seen it'. Converts model interpretation from verdict-on-output to steering-that-may-already-be-satisfied. ContextAssembly-layer change; event log already has the timestamps.\n\nR4 — rendering is free. Buffered (urmmluyq, parked) vs concurrent (mu-hsyt) is UI policy; neither satisfies nor violates R1-R3. Semantics live in the projection, not the viewport.\n\nR5 — primitive taxonomy (operator history with claude-code /btw): he used /btw heavily in week 1-2 then never again — wanted '/advise_current_prompt', got '/spawn_independent_claude_to_ask_something_it_wont_remember', which has NO known use-case for him. Two axes: context-inherited-in x exchange-contributes-back. steer = current/yes (the real /btw intent; R1-R3 govern it). fork/spawn = snapshot/no (honest divergence; the multi-session shared-starting-context future; relates to session-identity spec's /rewind=fork). fresh session = none/no (his parallel-work pattern today). The discarded-sidechain quadrant (current-ish/no) is the trap — tempting, contributes nothing. mu's /btw should be the STEER primitive; a context-inheriting spawn is a separate primitive (/fork or /spawn), not a /btw variant.\n\nBehavioral counterpart recorded in agent memory bf5b1b45 (reconcile-before-redo: check whether delivered work already satisfies a correction before mutating).","created_at":"2026-06-07T03:02:59Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-d29v","title":"t4c: presence probe ignores execute bit (non-exec file counts as installed)","description":"Found in post-merge review of PR #237 (mu-2332).\n\ncatalog::which_in (crates/t4c/src/catalog.rs:79-83) and snapshot::resolve_in_path (crates/t4c/src/snapshot.rs:404-413) both treat any Path::is_file() match on PATH as 'installed', without checking the execute bit.\n\nRepro (verified against the merged binary at 9dab42e in an isolated T4C_* sandbox): place a non-executable file named 'jj' (mode 0644) on PATH, run 't4c discover --json' -> bash.jj.status is reported PRESENT. A subsequent 't4c run bash.jj.status' would then fail to exec the non-runnable file. Same false-positive feeds the snapshot present-set and tool_fingerprint.\n\nSeverity: low (requires an oddly-named non-exec file on PATH). Hardening.\n\nSuggested fix: on unix, additionally require an execute bit (metadata mode & 0o111 != 0) in BOTH resolvers (which_in and resolve_in_path) so present == actually-runnable.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-06-07T17:36:06.188872804Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-07T17:36:06.188872804Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
