 {"id":"mu-d2iy","title":"t4c discovery-quality: ranking layer (chain/neighborhood + tombstone + embeddings)","description":"Add the discovery-QUALITY layer to t4c (crates/t4c, branch t4c-ranking off t4c-forward-build). Motivated by the mu-d33g cold-dogfood: token-overlap ranker + coarse catalog gave confident-WRONG find hits. Design (2026-05-29 conversation): (1) config grammar - a slot is either chain:[a,b,c] (interchangeable -> collapse to first-available, tombstone rest) OR distinct neighborhood entries (related but NOT interchangeable -> keep all, embeddings disambiguate); (2) discover resolves preference x availability STATICALLY and tombstones (3-state active/absent/superseded), then embeds the resolved set + caches vectors; (3) Embedder trait (FakeEmbedder deterministic + ConfigEmbedder reading ~/.config/agent/config.toml -> qwen3 endpoint); (4) SemanticRanker = cosine over cached vectors wired into find, preference baked at resolve NOT a runtime weight; (5) benchmark intent-sets (diff/compression/search, known answers) scored deterministically via FakeEmbedder. Small corpus => embed-all + brute cosine, no vector DB. usage-prior DEFERRED. STOP at the real-embedder re-dogfood + the judgment: does the blend make find earn its front-door role or concede to help/run. Worklist: br list --label goal:2026-05-29:SELF","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-05-29T08:58:27.006292882Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-05-29T09:31:06.361165623Z","closed_at":"2026-05-29T09:31:06.361076921Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":"mu","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":72,"issue_id":"mu-d2iy","author":"tcovert","text":"Worklist (goal:2026-05-29:mu-d2iy):\n  mu-d2iy.1 config grammar (chain vs neighborhood)   (root)\n  mu-d2iy.2 discover resolve + 3-state tombstone     (blockedBy mu-d2iy.1)\n  mu-d2iy.3 Embedder trait + Fake + Config           (blockedBy mu-d2iy.1)\n  mu-d2iy.4 SemanticRanker (cosine, cached) -> 