 {"id":"mu-d2iy.1","title":"config grammar: chain (collapse) vs neighborhood (keep+disambiguate)","description":"A slot is chain:[a,b,c] (interchangeable, collapse to first-available, tombstone rest) OR distinct neighborhood entries (related but not interchangeable, keep all). Parser + types; author tags synonyms-vs-neighbors. Examples: chains grep=[rg,grep], find=[fd,find], ls=[eza,exa,ls], compress=[zstd,pixz,xz,gzip]; neighborhood: diff family (delta/colordiff/diff a chain-inside; diff3 distinct). Tests on example configs.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-29T08:58:27.197954077Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-05-29T09:03:27.138355315Z","closed_at":"2026-05-29T09:03:27.138273653Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":"mu","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["goal:2026-05-29:mu-d2iy"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mu-d2iy.1","depends_on_id":"mu-d2iy","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-05-29T08:58:27.197954077Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
