 {"id":"mu-mu-console-operator-web-jg9p.9","title":"mu-solo: add light links/commands to open web-console views","description":"After the first web-console pages exist, add light mu-solo affordances that point to them instead of duplicating rich dashboards in the TUI.\n\nExamples:\n- command to open current session in web console\n- status/menu hint when console is configured\n- maybe copy/open URL for current model call/context assembly\n\nAcceptance:\n- TUI remains a cockpit, not a bad browser.\n- Useful rich views have a one-keystroke/command path from mu-solo.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-06-05T09:27:29.972035791Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T09:27:29.972035791Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["mu-console","mu-solo","tui","ux"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mu-mu-console-operator-web-jg9p.9","depends_on_id":"mu-mu-console-operator-web-jg9p","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-05T09:27:29.972035791Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"mu-mu-native-config-sources-98j7","title":"mu-native config & skill sources: drop .pi / .claude-personal borrows","description":"mu currently borrows the operator's personal agent config at startup instead of reading mu-native files. Two hardcoded borrows:\n\nA) Project-context files: crates/mu-core/src/context/recall/project_files.rs DEFAULT_FILES_IN_ORDER hardcodes ~/.claude-personal/CLAUDE.md, ~/CLAUDE.md, ~/.pi/agent/AGENTS.md (lines 41-47). The doc comment already anticipates the ~/.config/mu/ migration ('separate bead, not yet filed').\n\nB) Skills dirs: default_search_dirs duplicated in crates/mu-core/src/skill/loader.rs:189 AND crates/mu-solo/src/skills.rs:277 — both push ~/.claude-personal/skills as a 'compat-read'.\n\nDecision (operator, 2026-06-07): go mu-native, DROP the borrows entirely. Default to ~/.config/mu/{CLAUDE,AGENTS}.md for project files and ~/.config/mu/skills for skills (alongside ./project-local and .mu/skills). Remove the .claude-personal / .pi / ~/CLAUDE.md entries. Route through the existing mu_core::config::Config where natural so paths are overridable, not re-hardcoded. Keep ./CLAUDE.md + ./AGENTS.md (project-root) and .mu/skills (project-local).\n\nAcceptance: no source path under crates/ (excluding tests/comments) references .claude-personal or .pi for live config/skill loading; defaults resolve under ~/.config/mu; just ci green.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-08T03:01:27.328802925Z","created_by":"cc-personal","updated_at":"2026-06-08T06:26:23.047248735Z","closed_at":"2026-06-08T06:26:23.047179013Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"mu-mu-own-context-config-kfqz","title":"mu: own config/context files separate from claude-code — make recall file list configurable + ~/.config/mu/ migration","description":"Operator goal (tcovert 2026-06-07, discovered via truss /tmp/mu.truss to see what files mu opens at start): mu should load its OWN context/config files, separate from what it shares with claude-code and pi-rust. mu is the experimentation runtime and wants different rules/context than the shared CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md — e.g. a dedicated ~/.config/mu/AGENTS.md or MU.md — rather than always sharing.\n\nCURRENT STATE: crates/mu-core/src/context/recall/project_files.rs hardcodes the hierarchy:\n  DEFAULT_FILES_IN_ORDER = [ ./CLAUDE.md, ./AGENTS.md, ~/.claude-personal/CLAUDE.md, ~/CLAUDE.md, ~/.pi/agent/AGENTS.md ]\n- ProjectFileRecallProvider::new() uses DEFAULT_FILES_IN_ORDER; a with_files(iter) constructor EXISTS but nothing wires config -> with_files (likely test-only).\n- The [recall] config section (mu-core/src/config.rs RecallConfig) is only a session-start-injection TOGGLE, not a file list.\n- The module doc references an UNFILED todo: '~/.config/mu/ migration (separate bead, not yet filed)' under which ~/.pi/agent/AGENTS.md becomes ~/.config/mu/AGENTS.md. THIS BEAD files it.\n\nASKS:\n1. Make the recall file list CONFIGURABLE — add e.g. [recall] files = [\"./MU.md\", \"~/.config/mu/AGENTS.md\", ...] that, when present, overrides DEFAULT_FILES_IN_ORDER (wire config -> the existing with_files()). Keep the default for back-comat.\n2. Establish ~/.config/mu/ as mu's own config dir and add mu-specific context files (MU.md / ~/.config/mu/AGENTS.md) to the default-or-example hierarchy, so mu can diverge from claude-code/pi context. (Subsumes the in-code unfiled migration TODO; update that doc comment + DEFAULT_FILES_IN_ORDER line.)\n3. DISCOVERABILITY (operator had to use truss to learn what files load): a /context (or /files) command and/or a startup log line listing exactly which context files were read (and which were skipped-missing). Same recurring discoverability tax as mu-tooling-inventory-aaj0 and the mu-solo route-list gap (mu-mu-solo-loop-terminate-5ek5 comment).\n\nWHY: separate experimentation context from production claude-code rules; stop sharing one set of rules across tools with different purposes; stop needing to grep source / truss to know what mu loads.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-08T02:17:13.760471147Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-08T02:17:13.760471147Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"mu-mu-solo-loop-terminate-5ek5","title":"mu-solo: session loop terminates mid-session + /q doesn't exit + startup route-switch failures","description":"Reported by tcovert 2026-06-07 on threadripper (mu). mu-solo, started anthropic-api/claude-sonnet-4-6, truss attached to the process at start. Trace saved: /tmp/mu.truss on threadripper (1.88 GB — grep targeted, do not read whole).\n\nTHREE symptoms (possibly related):\n\n1. STARTUP ROUTE FAILURES. On launch:\n   - 'provider switch failed: RPC session.set_route error {code:-32602, invalid set_route pa[rams]}'\n   - 'model switch failed: RPC session.set_route error {code:-32602, unknown route anthropic[...]}'  (x2)\n   - then 'switched -> openai_codex / gpt-5.5' (x2).\n   Started as anthropic-api/sonnet-4-6 but ended up on openai_codex/gpt-5.5 — the anthropic route appears not registered/resolvable at set_route time, and it silently falls back. -32602 = invalid params (JSON-RPC). Smells like a route-registration/ordering bug at session init.\n\n2. SESSION LOOP TERMINATED (the serious one). Conversation worked initially ('hello?' -> assistant replied). User then asked it to READ /tmp/mu.truss ('figure out how mu gets initial context'). After that, all subsequent asks ('ping','hello?') returned:\n   'ask failed: {code:-32603, message:\"session loop has terminated\"}'  (-32603 = internal error).\n   The agent loop thread died/panicked; the frontend stayed up but every ask fails. Trigger correlates with the read-file/tool turn (possibly reading the 1.88GB truss file itself blew up the loop — OOM / huge-file read / context overflow?). Needs the loop's stderr/panic + whether the read tool tried to slurp 1.88GB.\n\n3. /q DID NOT EXIT (quit hang). Program didn't exit on quit after the loop terminated — likely the frontend waits on a dead loop thread / a join that never returns. Quit path should be robust to a terminated loop.\n\nNOTES: truss (ptrace) attached at start may influence signal/timing; confirm repro WITHOUT truss. Likely an interaction: loop panic on the read turn -> set_route/ask RPCs fail -> quit join hangs. INVESTIGATE: (a) loop panic cause on the read-file turn (check if read tried 1.88GB), (b) route registration so anthropic resolves at init, (c) make /q force-exit even with a dead loop. Evidence: /tmp/mu.truss (threadripper).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-06-08T02:07:21.101219914Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-08T02:10:04.496524555Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":241,"issue_id":"mu-mu-solo-loop-terminate-5ek5","author":"tcovert","text":"CORRECTION on symptom #1 (operator, 2026-06-07): the startup route-switch failures are NOT a route-registration bug — they are a DISCOVERABILITY gap. The valid provider/model names + aliases are not listed anywhere the operator can see them (not in mu-solo, not in the config), so the operator had to RIPGREP THE REPO to find what to put into mu, guessed wrong, and set_route correctly rejected the guesses (-32602 invalid params / unknown route). So #1 is reclassified: not a bug, a UX/discoverability improvement.\n\nREAL FIX for #1 (separate from the #2/#3 loop crash):\n- Surface valid routes in mu-solo: a /providers and/or /models (or /routes) command listing registered provider + model + aliases.\n- On a FAILED set_route, the error should ENUMERATE valid routes (\\\"unknown route anthropic; valid: anthropic-api/claude-sonnet-4-6, openai_codex/gpt-5.5, ...\\\") instead of a bare invalid-params code.\n- Document the route names/aliases in the config / a discoverable place so the operator never has to grep source.\nThis is the same recurring discoverability tax as bead mu-tooling-inventory-aaj0 (tools/tests undiscoverable -> grep each time); consider tackling together. Recommend SPLITTING #1 into its own enhancement bead and keeping THIS bead focused on the #2 loop-termination crash (likely 1.88GB read) + #3 /q hang.","created_at":"2026-06-08T02:10:04Z"}]}
