 truss. Likely an interaction: loop panic on the read turn -> set_route/ask RPCs fail -> quit join hangs. INVESTIGATE: (a) loop panic cause on the read-file turn (check if read tried 1.88GB), (b) route registration so anthropic resolves at init, (c) make /q force-exit even with a dead loop. Evidence: /tmp/mu.truss (threadripper).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-06-08T02:07:21.101219914Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-11T19:46:01.596648765Z","closed_at":"2026-06-11T19:46:01.596552203Z","close_reason":"Symptoms #2/#3 fixed (root cause: uncapped verbatim read + tiktoken quadratic whitespace regex panicking inline compaction in the loop task; /q never killed the child and skipped terminal restore on unwind). Read cap + ranged reads, tool/compaction panic isolation, >1MB chars/4 estimate guard, TerminalRestoreGuard + bounded shutdown_child. Symptom #1 split to mu-solo-route-discoverability-tazd. Lands with the mu-solo operability PR.","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":241,"issue_id":"mu-mu-solo-loop-terminate-5ek5","author":"tcovert","text":"CORRECTION on symptom #1 (operator, 2026-06-07): the startup route-switch failures are NOT a route-registration bug — they are a DISCOVERABILITY gap. The valid provider/model names + aliases are not listed anywhere the operator can see them (not in mu-solo, not in the config), so the operator had to RIPGREP THE REPO to find what to put into mu, guessed wrong, and set_route correctly rejected the guesses (-32602 invalid params / unknown route). So #1 is reclassified: not a bug, a UX/discoverability improvement.\n\nREAL FIX for #1 (separate from the #2/#3 loop crash):\n- Surface valid routes in mu-solo: a /providers and/or /models (or /routes) command listing registered provider + model + aliases.\n- On a FAILED set_route, the error should ENUMERATE valid routes (\\\"unknown route anthropic; valid: anthropic-api/claude-sonnet-4-6, openai_codex/gpt-5.5, ...\\\") instead of a bare invalid-params code.\n- Document the route names/aliases in the config / a discoverable place so the operator never has to grep source.\nThis is the same recurring discoverability tax as bead mu-tooling-inventory-aaj0 (tools/tests undiscoverable -> grep each time); consider tackling together. Recommend SPLITTING #1 into its own enhancement bead and keeping THIS bead focused on the #2 loop-termination crash (likely 1.88GB read) + #3 /q hang.","created_at":"2026-06-08T02:10:04Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-mu036-accepted-semantics-vx9c","title":"mu-036: 'accepted: true' means enqueued, not honored — decide RPC semantics for non-autonomous targets","description":"Surfaced by codex/gpt-5.5 review of PR (mu-28u Phase C), 2026-06-06: both session.start_autonomous AND session.schedule_wakeup return accepted:true on input-channel enqueue; the loop may then decline (schedule_wakeup on a non-autonomous session declines with a warning callout). A caller can get accepted:true with nothing scheduled. PRE-EXISTING shape (Phase B established it); Phase C inherited it consistently.\n\nDESIGN DECISION (operator): (a) handler pre-checks session RunMode (racy but honest best-effort), (b) document accepted = 'delivered to session' and add a follow-up notification/event for declined inputs (the warning callout already lands durably), or (c) loop-side ack via oneshot (sync RPC, strongest semantics, most plumbing). Spec mu-036 does not answer it — that is why this is a bead and not a fix.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-06-06T09:37:01.254889180Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-06T09:37:01.254889180Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["autonomous","mu-036","protocol"]}
 {"id":"mu-mucm","title":"mu stats: session-metrics projection layer (DuckDB over event JSONL) + dashboard","description":"Aggregation + visualization over the durable event logs, so session economics/shape analysis (like the 2026-06-04 replay readout) is repeatable and visual instead of ad-hoc jq.\n\nWHY DUCKDB: in-process OLAP, queries JSONL directly (read_json over ~/.local/share/mu/events/*/*.jsonl) — zero ETL, the event log stays the single source of truth (the mu thesis). Projections are just SQL views: cost per session (join task_telemetry to pricing), context trajectory (context_assembly.token_count_estimate ordered by event id), token_breakdown composition over time, cache hit/expiry detection (gap analysis on telemetry timestamps), compaction events, tool mix.\n\nPHASES: (1) saved SQL views + CLI entry point ('mu stats' or sidecar script); (2) dashboard page — static HTML + vega-lite fed by query JSON, or mu-native 'mu stats serve'. Operator explicitly wants visuals/navigable projections ('you may be able to keep it all in your head, having visuals will help me').\n\nREFERENCE QUERIES: the analyses in ~/.claude-personal/experiments/replay-economics-2026-06-04.md (trajectory, TTL simulation, composition at first/peak/last, eviction breakdown) are the spec — each should become a view.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-04T21:45:03.528750098Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-08T08:02:41.525824502Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":132,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"DEPLOYMENT CONSTRAINT (tcovert 2026-06-04): do NOT install duckdb on the host. Target = the new jail (in progress); operator checking FreeBSD ports for duckdb first. Design-only until then. Host-safe interim option if wanted sooner: same views in stdlib sqlite3, schema kept portable to duckdb.","created_at":"2026-06-04T21:48:28Z"},{"id":133,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"PROTOTYPE LANDED (2026-06-04, host — operator installed duckdb + py311-duckdb from ports, lifting the earlier constraint): ~/src/claude-personal/scripts/mu_stats.sql (views: mu_events, ask_telemetry w/ gap+expiry detection, session_costs, context_trajectory, compactions, tool_mix) + gen_mu_dashboard.py (self-contained vega-lite HTML -> ~/mu-stats/dashboard.html). Found 981 sessions / 41 priced; calibration anchors reproduce exactly ($8.62 + 4 gaps, $4.08 + 0). NOTE: ~/.local/bin/python3 shadows ports python — use /usr/local/bin/python3.11. Remaining for the bead: mu-native 'mu stats' entry point, more views (token_breakdown composition over time, compaction decision detail), jail deployment if desired.","created_at":"2026-06-04T21:53:31Z"},{"id":137,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"WAVE-0b SPEC (2026-06-05, telemetry-first wave; companion to mu-cache-write-tier-split-umq6 — field names locked between them):\n\n1. ask_telemetry mu leg: add cw_5m / cw_1h columns from payload.cache_write_5m_tokens / payload.cache_write_1h_tokens (COALESCE 0; NULL-safe on all pre-split sessions).\n2. session_costs: when split present, write cost = 1.25x*cw_5m + 2.0x*cw_1h (proven tier); else current inferred behavior. CALIBRATION ANCHORS MUST REPRODUCE ($8.62 + 4 gaps, $4.08 + 0 — see replay-economics-2026-06-04.md).\n3. NEW view compaction_stats: aggregate over compactions BY POLICY — n, total_ms, mean_ms, p0/p50/p99/p100 (quantile_cont on wall_clock_ms), mean reduction_pct. Per-session detail stays the existing raw-rows compactions view (operator decision 2026-06-05: no per-session percentiles — n=1-3 percentiles mislead, averages hide; raw rows + by-policy aggregate only).\n4. gen_mu_dashboard.py: compaction panel (by-policy percentile table; duration scatter if cheap) + per-tier write columns on the session table; mark proven vs inferred tier.","created_at":"2026-06-05T07:09:49Z"},{"id":161,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"SESSION-QUALITY MARKS + CC-SESSION UNIFICATION (operator-ratified 2026-06-05 evening; context: postmortem-2026-06-05-relitigation-session + the weekend-degradation hypothesis — terrain: incident-flavored task_log entries 16.5% Sun-UTC vs 4-6% weekday baseline; mu-on-API-key showed the same ailment as claude-code the same night, so the billing-path discriminator is dead).\n\nMOTIVATION: event logs persist but carry no operator judgment — without a mark we can't label which sessions were degraded, so they can't feed analysis or the replay-probe canary (byte-identical degraded-session prefixes re-run across days/times, N samples, scored for relitigation/contradiction-of-context — difficulty controlled exactly, time the only free variable).\n\nPROJECTION-LAYER WORK (this bead, phase-2 scope):\n1. cc_sessions view in mu_stats.sql — decode claude-code transcripts (~/.claude-personal/projects/*/*.jsonl) with the SAME read_ndjson_objects pattern t4c_tool_inventory.sql already proves (tools.html decodes cc today; the Sessions page doesn't yet). Pull session id, model, timestamps, usage. Sessions page shows both corpora.\n2. session_marks view — UNION of (a) mu OperatorMark events from the event logs (see split-out mu bead for the event/console/CLI side) and (b) cc-session marks stored as task_log rows: tag session-mark, session_ref = cc session id (column already exists in task_log schema, currently unused). DuckDB reads task_log.sqlite via sqlite_scanner.\n3. Dashboard: mark-rate by day-of-week alongside the existing charts (the oxygen-hypothesis instrument); marked-bad list = the replay-fixture queue by query.\n\nCAPTURE DOCTRINE: mu marks live IN the event log (single-source-of-truth thesis, immutable, re-mark = newer event); cc transcripts are app-owned so cc marks live in the task_log sidecar, never appended to claude's jsonl.\n\nFirst fixtures already identified: mu session 3dd40c3c1f84f278 (2026-06-05 21:23, dismissed unimpressed) and the 2026-06-05 claude-code relitigation session.","created_at":"2026-06-06T03:51:47Z"},{"id":188,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"RE-SPEC (operator direction 2026-06-06, refactor review): two observability surfaces are disjoint and need consolidation + refactoring —\n(a) mu-console (axum, live): http://localhost:18769/mu-console/sessions — in-repo, serves sessions index/detail/economics/explorers; PR #215 already folded the daemon-dashboard INTO the console ('one surface for console+dashboard'), so the console is the convergence target.\n(b) mu-stats (static, hourly cron): http://localhost/mu-stats/dashboard.html — generated OUTSIDE the repo by ~/src/claude-personal/scripts/gen_mu_dashboard.py over mu_stats.sql DuckDB views (billing reconciliation, anomaly worklist, compaction panels, session-quality marks).\n\nDirection: connect (b) into (a). Options at sprint time: console gains a /mu-console/stats page rendering the same views (DuckDB invoked server-side, or the SQL ported to the console's native scan layer); OR console links out to the static page as a first step (cheap, the jg9p.9 bead pattern). Either way the native 'mu stats' CLI entry point (original phase 1 remainder, still absent from mu.rs subcommands) should share the projection code with the console rather than growing a third implementation. Operator history note: he spent long minutes in a prior session just FINDING where these lived — discoverability of the surfaces is part of the bead (link them from each other + README).","created_at":"2026-06-07T03:58:31Z"},{"id":249,"issue_id":"mu-mucm","author":"tcovert","text":"DIRECTION CHANGED 2026-06-08: operator chose STATIC-LEAN, no standing live service. The earlier RE-SPEC here ('connect static mu-stats INTO the axum mu-console') is SUPERSEDED. New work split out: mu-07xl (consolidate static pages into one surface + add deploy/install step; axum console = on-demand only, never a standing service) and mu-vb8h (broaden claude-code coverage to all accounts × all project dirs — the real cause of 'mu-only' marks + scanner gaps). The hand-started :18769 console was a stale orphan and was killed.","created_at":"2026-06-08T08:02:41Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-mucm.1","title":"stats: unify mu and cc session marks view","description":"Extend the stats/projection layer with session_marks view that UNIONs mu OperatorMark events from mu event logs and Claude Code marks from task_log.sqlite rows tagged session-mark/session_ref. Acceptance: query can list marked-bad sessions across both fleets with provider/session_id/rating/note/timestamp/source columns, ready for dashboard mark-rate and replay-fixture queue.","notes":"SCOPE ADDITION (operator, 2026-06-06): alongside session_marks, add a session_incidents projection (or LEFT JOIN onto session_marks) reading task_log.sqlite rows tagged incident-ref: session_ref (fleet-prefixed: 'cc:<uuid>' / 'mu:<daemon>/<session>'), description (incident slug), result (report path). Purpose: chain of custody — incident report ↔ session event log ↔ operator mark, queryable in one place. Backfilled exemplar rows exist: 9f13ea8a (cc relitigation session, fixture #2), 7a4a7adb (mu 3dd40c3c, fixture #1, marked 3/5). Field names locked with lqqt.3's notes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cc-personal-c5b85cc9","created_at":"2026-06-06T06:58:21.025052043Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-06T08:25:15.880826577Z","closed_at":"2026-06-06T08:25:15.880745195Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"c5b85cc9-6a12-4a0f-ae2e-65f086b690e6","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cc-sessions","dashboard","goal:2026-06-06:3prb","marks","overnight","stats"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"mu-mucm.1","depends_on_id":"mu-cc-sessions-console-lqqt.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-06-06T07:28:02.681086513Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"mu-mucm.1","depends_on_id":"mu-mucm","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-06T06:58:21.025052043Z","created_by":"tcovert","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
