 {"id":"mu-solo-notify-occasion-56h0","title":"mu-solo: notifications never fire under zellij — delegate focus-gating to kitty via OSC 99 o=invisible","description":"Follow-up to mu-solo-osc-notify-mbmn (PR #197). Operator field test: no popup after switching away during a turn. ROOT CAUSE (measured): zellij does not forward focus reporting (?1004) to panes at all — operator's cat -v test showed no ^[[I/^[[O even on pane switches — so terminal_focused stays true forever and the app-side gate never opens (designed conservative silence, wrong terminal). FIX (operator semantics: 'ignore zellij, have kitty do the work; pane switches silent, tab/app switches notify'): emit always, with OSC 99 metadata o=invisible — kitty shows the notification only when the window is in an inactive tab or its OS window is inactive (spec verbatim match). Drop the app-side focus check from the emission condition; keep focus-event tracking harmless. Claude code parity confirmed: cc natively notifies only in ghostty/kitty/iterm2 (terminal-config docs) and breaks under tmux for the same OSC-forwarding reason (cc issue #19976).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-personal-ec4a0b48","created_at":"2026-06-05T22:39:59.225278536Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-06T19:35:11.626606437Z","closed_at":"2026-06-05T22:47:57.095862289Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"ec4a0b48-9dd9-4d05-8867-03bcfa5b8b0e","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":175,"issue_id":"mu-solo-notify-occasion-56h0","author":"tcovert","text":"MEASUREMENT CORRECTED (2026-06-06): this bead's 'zellij forwards no ?1004 focus reporting at all (operator-measured)' is disproven by an operator raw probe on zellij 0.44.3 (printf '\\e[?1004h'; cat -v → ^[[O/^[[I on pane switches). Either the original measurement was faulty or zellij gained pane-level 1004 forwarding between versions. The o=invisible design this bead chose on that basis was reversed in PR #212 (bead mu-solo-notify-pane-focus-jqnp).","created_at":"2026-06-06T19:35:11Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-solo-notify-pane-focus-jqnp","title":"mu-solo notifications: only fire on app switch — kitty suppresses focused-window OSC; gate at pane level + o=always","description":"Operator report 2026-06-06: mbmn's notifications only manifest when switching to another APP, never when in another zellij pane. ROOT CAUSE (one layer above the escape choice): kitty's policy suppresses notifications from the focused window; zellij panes are invisible to kitty, so pane-switches never unsuppress. mu-solo's existing focus gate is ALSO app-level in effect (kitty forwards pane-level 1004 via zellij — mu-solo knows pane focus, but kitty still suppresses the popup).\n\nFIX: (1) emit OSC 99 with o=always (kitty's when-to-show override) so kitty displays regardless of window focus; (2) keep/raise the gating decision in mu-solo using its PANE-level focus knowledge (app.rs terminal_focused via zellij-proxied 1004) — notify when pane-unfocused, stay silent when the operator is looking at the pane. The layer with the information makes the decision.\n\nFALLBACK MATRIX (terrain-test each in zellij-in-kitty/FreeBSD before depth-committing — memory enumerate-mechanism-space-before-implementing): BEL + WM urgency hint; OSC 777;notify; title-change + WM rule; kitten notify via remote control; daemon-side notify-send/libnotify (bypasses zellij AND kitty policy entirely — strongest fallback if a notification daemon runs). Verify zellij passthrough per mechanism (printf to /dev/tty from inside a pane).\n\nAcceptance: working in another zellij pane (same kitty window), a session.done/input_required in mu-solo raises a visible desktop popup; sitting IN the mu-solo pane raises none.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-06-06T19:10:53.872345333Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-06T19:35:11.538748579Z","closed_at":"2026-06-06T19:28:46.042370674Z","close_reason":"PR #212 merged: o=invisible→o=always + pane-level should_notify gate (terminal_focused via zellij-proxied 1004). Reverses 56h0's 'zellij forwards no ?1004' measurement on behavioral evidence (claude-code recap-on-pane-switch, operator-observed 2026-06-06); raw probe not yet run — operator chair test is acceptance and settles the terrain dispute. Failure mode if 56h0 was right: conservative silence.","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["mu-solo","notifications","tui"],"comments":[{"id":174,"issue_id":"mu-solo-notify-pane-focus-jqnp","author":"tcovert","text":"TERRAIN SETTLED (operator raw probe, 2026-06-06 15:32): printf '\\e[?1004h'; cat -v in a zellij pane shows ^[[O/^[[I pairs on every pane switch out/in — zellij 0.44.3 forwards 1004 at pane granularity, per-application (only the enabling pane gets events, only about its own focus). PR #212's gate confirmed to have its signal. Remaining acceptance: the chair test against rebuilt mu-solo (popup from another pane; silence in-pane).","created_at":"2026-06-06T19:35:11Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-solo-osc-notify-mbmn","title":"mu-solo: desktop notifications via terminal escape (OSC 9/99) — turn done / input required","description":"Operator request 2026-06-05, modeled on claude code's notifications ('Claude is waiting for your input' / 'needs your input on ...' — app emits OSC 9, enclosing kitty raises the desktop notification with its own logo). Add to mu-solo: (1) NOTIFY EVENTS: session.done -> 'mu is waiting for your input' (include short model/elapsed context); session.error -> error notice; input_required/approval (if mu-solo surfaces approvals) -> 'mu needs your approval: <tool> <arg>'. (2) FOCUS GATING: only notify when the terminal is UNFOCUSED — crossterm EnableFocusChange + Event::FocusGained/FocusLost tracked as focused:bool; notifying the focused terminal is noise. (3) ESCAPE CHOICE: OSC 9 (ESC ] 9 ; body BEL) as the broadly-supported baseline (kitty, wezterm, iTerm2); optionally OSC 99 kitty-native (title+body) when TERM contains kitty. (4) CONFIG: tui.notifications bool, default on. TERRAIN CHECKS at impl: zellij passthrough of OSC 9 to the host terminal (operator runs zellij-in-kitty; verify with printf '\\\\x1b]9;test\\\\x07' > /dev/tty inside zellij); interaction with the inline viewport (escape must go to the tty raw, not through ratatui's buffer). Consider min-elapsed threshold later if quick turns get spammy.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-personal-ec4a0b48","created_at":"2026-06-05T20:55:35.175914699Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T21:33:32.106332563Z","closed_at":"2026-06-05T21:33:32.106246631Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"ec4a0b48-9dd9-4d05-8867-03bcfa5b8b0e","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"mu-solo-route-discoverability-tazd","title":"mu-solo: route discoverability — /routes listing + set_route errors that enumerate valid routes","description":"Split from mu-mu-solo-loop-terminate-5ek5 per operator comment 2026-06-08: the startup set_route failures were correct rejections of guessed names — the real gap is discoverability. Fix: (a) /routes (and/or /providers, /models) command in mu-solo listing registered provider/model/aliases from daemon.list_routes; (b) failed set_route error enumerates valid routes instead of bare -32602; (c) document route names in example config. Same discoverability tax family as mu-tooling-inventory-aaj0. Groundwork for the mu-048 /model picker.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-11T18:52:00.017247969Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-11T18:52:00.017247969Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"mu-solo-scrollback-dup-recommit-8hva","title":"mu-solo: duplicated mid-message span in scrollback — overlapping re-commit of streamed text","description":"SYMPTOM (operator-supplied transcript copy, 2026-06-05, the jg9p.1 parallel session): the assistant's final message rendered with a verbatim duplicated span — '...This turns it into a comfortable history reader.\\n\\n### 2. Compare two sessions/runs...maybe side-by-side prompt/cost timeline' appears twice back-to-back; text before the span once, span twice, tail once.\n\nEVIDENCE IT IS A RENDERER BUG, NOT MODEL OUTPUT: durable event log daemon 2f270bcba43f305d session-1 — the final assistant_message_event contains the span EXACTLY ONCE (grep -o count = 1). The duplication exists only in mu-solo's rendered scrollback.\n\nSHAPE => MECHANISM HYPOTHESIS: before-once / span-twice / tail-once is an OVERLAPPING RE-COMMIT — the live streaming block was committed to native scrollback up to boundary A during streaming (insert_before), then a subsequent commit (finalize, viewport overflow, resize/mode flip, or next-chunk flush) re-emitted starting from an earlier block/paragraph boundary B < A instead of resuming at the exact committed offset. The duplicated region is precisely [B, A].\n\nSUSPECT CODE: crates/mu-solo/src/viewport.rs — transcript via insert_before into mux scrollback (module doc line 6); multiple insert_before call sites (564, 603, 839, 850, 871, 1308); assistant_text_finalized handling (~line 260, default off). The turn included multiple tool_call/tool_result blocks before the long final message — interleaving may matter.\n\nREPRO POINTER: session events at ~/.local/share/mu/events/2f270bcba43f305d/session-1.jsonl — replaying that event sequence through the renderer should reproduce; the message is long (multi-screen), streamed, and follows several Bash tool blocks. Distinctive grep: 'highest-leverage analytical feature'.\n\nRELATED: mu-wf5w (inverse failure — live block never commits, turn LOST: same commit machinery, opposite direction; a fix should consider both), mu-d04a (live-viewport streaming + commit-on-finalize design), mu-vi6n (dump-on-flip re-render). A correct fix likely makes the committed-offset tracking exact (byte/line offset into the finalized text, not block boundaries) and idempotent (commit_from(offset) where offset = exactly what's already in scrollback).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-personal-0901bc4a","created_at":"2026-06-05T15:38:28.726235662Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T17:34:55.802047502Z","closed_at":"2026-06-05T17:34:55.801951450Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"0901bc4a-f9f2-4f7a-9e93-6babbe85dc37","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["mu-solo","rendering","scrollback"],"comments":[{"id":139,"issue_id":"mu-solo-scrollback-dup-recommit-8hva","author":"tcovert","text":"Operator note (2026-06-05): prior incidents of this flavor have ALSO been viewer-side with consistent events — recurring pattern, not a one-off. Implication for the fix: don't spot-patch the one insert_before site that misfired; make the scrollback commit protocol structurally idempotent (track exact committed offset into finalized text; commit_from(offset) only emits the uncommitted suffix). The event log has repeatedly proven to be the trustworthy layer — keep treating it as the source of truth the renderer must converge to, and consider a debug assertion/diagnostic comparing committed-scrollback length vs event content length at finalize (the renderer-mismatch diagnostic pattern already exists in mu-solo for faux-fallback visibility).","created_at":"2026-06-05T15:38:48Z"},{"id":140,"issue_id":"mu-solo-scrollback-dup-recommit-8hva","author":"tcovert","text":"Design rationale pinned (tcovert, 2026-06-05): the renderer journal is ALWAYS-AVAILABLE (runtime knob, release builds) deliberately — planned topology has the UI running anywhere with mu-solo remote from the daemon. In that world the semantic event store is server-side and the rendering is client-side: a viewer bug cannot be diagnosed from server logs by construction, and the LOCAL journal is the only record of what the terminal did. Do not later remove the journal as 'redundant with the event log' — the redundancy only exists in the co-located topology. Verbose diagnostics remain compile-gated (debugrelease profile, memory 7bc10cf4); the flight-recorder tier stays in release.","created_at":"2026-06-05T15:45:26Z"}]}
 {"id":"mu-solo-shift-enter-62tx","title":"mu-solo: Shift+Enter inserts newline in the prompt (multi-line input)","description":"Plain Enter submits; any modified Enter (Shift/Alt/Ctrl) should insert '\\n' into the prompt instead, mirroring mu-tui's convention (mu-tui main.rs on_key_send_prompt). Two missing pieces: (1) bin/mu-solo.rs never pushes KeyboardEnhancementFlags::DISAMBIGUATE_ESCAPE_CODES, so kitty-protocol terminals (incl. zellij) deliver Shift+Enter as plain CR — push after enable_raw_mode, pop on teardown, mu-tui precedent main.rs:4809/4833. (2) app.rs handle_key has no modified-Enter arm — add one before the plain-Enter submit arm; also add Ctrl-J as the historical newline fallback for terminals that strip the modifier. InputBuffer + render_viewport are already multi-line-capable (paste path proves it; input.rs doc comment anticipates this feature). Event loop already filters KeyEventKind::Press so no Release-event hazard.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"cc-personal-ec4a0b48","created_at":"2026-06-05T18:06:24.885445519Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T18:20:27.900947943Z","closed_at":"2026-06-05T18:20:27.900864481Z","close_reason":"done","closed_by_session":"ec4a0b48-9dd9-4d05-8867-03bcfa5b8b0e","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"mu-solo-teardown-panic-guard-s0fn","title":"mu-solo: panic-safe terminal teardown (raw mode, bracketed paste, keyboard flags, focus reporting)","description":"From the qwen3.6:27b round-4 review of mu-solo-osc-notify-mbmn (the one finding worth keeping): if app.run() panics, unwind skips the teardown sequence in bin/mu-solo.rs (disable_raw_mode, DisableBracketedPaste, PopKeyboardEnhancementFlags, DisableFocusChange) leaving the terminal in raw mode with enhancements active. Pre-existing pattern for ALL four — the osc-notify diff merely added a fourth member. Fix: a Drop-guard struct constructed after enable_raw_mode that performs the full teardown in drop(), so unwind and early-return share one cleanup path; the explicit teardown lines become the guard going out of scope. Cite: mu-tui's leave_terminal_mode has the same exposure — consider fixing both or sharing the guard.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-06-05T21:31:53.750240746Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T21:31:53.750240746Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"mu-solo-window-title-2f64","title":"mu-solo: dynamic window title — mu char + throbber + session name/rename (claude-code style)","description":"Operator request 2026-06-05. Set/update the terminal window title from mu-solo, like claude code does. Proposed format: 'μ <throbber> <name/alias> <daemon:session> - <task>'. Pieces: (1) title plumbing — crossterm SetTitle; mu-tui precedent exists (mu_terminal_title + SetTitle in enter_terminal_mode); mu-solo currently sets no title. Update on state transitions and/or render tick. (2) Session name/alias concept + a /rename command (claude-code-style naming); decide where the name lives (client-only vs daemon session metadata — daemon metadata survives reattach and shows in mu-console). (3) Throbber in the title, animated per tick while a turn is live. OPEN DESIGN QUESTIONS (operator's, to settle before/at impl): (a) should the throbber be color-coded? NOTE terrain constraint: window titles are plain text — no color possible in the title itself; color-coding can only apply to the in-TUI statusline throbber, so this question may split into title-throbber (mono) + statusline-throbber (could color-code by provider_status state, e.g. awaiting_first_token vs thinking vs tool_executing). (b) should the title throbber alternate between the mu char and the throbbing cycle frames (i.e. μ is itself a frame), vs static 'μ' prefix + separate spinner? Also decide title restore-on-exit behavior (save/restore old title vs set to empty).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-06-05T18:15:41.508446662Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-05T18:15:41.508446662Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"mu-solo-zellij-blank-band-ptvm","title":"mu-solo: blank band (~viewport height) in scrollback after a large turn commit under zellij","description":"Operator repro 2026-06-05, FIRST FLIGHT-RECORDER CASE (debugrelease build, all of today's PRs incl. 8hva fix). SYMPTOM: after a review-length turn, the visible scrollback shows a ~14-row blank band between the (preview-truncated) Read tool block and the final assistant text; content above the band exists but was pushed out of view. EVIDENCE: renderer journal (~/.local/share/mu/solo/renderer.jsonl, ts 1780696610914..1780697008437) is CONTIGUOUS — commits 0-3, 3-7, then ONE 388-line insert_before (the review answer block), ZERO finalize-mismatch records — so in-memory history accounting believes everything landed; the screen disagrees. Operator's screen paste preserved in session transcript. HYPOTHESES (viewport.rs insert_before): (a) the push-viewport-down branch emits DECSTBM + CSI T (reverse scroll within margins) — zellij's handling of margined reverse-scroll may blank-fill instead of moving content; (b) the main emission path scrolls 388 lines through a top-margin-1 region bottom (codex-rs pattern) — verified to feed scrollback on kitty/xterm, UNVERIFIED through zellij's compositor, and the operator runs zellij-in-kitty; (c) interaction with sync-output ?2026 under zellij. The band size ~viewport height suggests the OLD viewport rows were vacated (viewport moved/scrolled) but never repainted/backfilled by the multiplexer. REPRO PATH: drive mu-solo inside a zellij session with a turn whose commit greatly exceeds terminal height; capture ground truth with 'zellij action dump-screen' immediately after; diff against renderer journal history slice. Also test the same commit in BARE kitty to bisect zellij vs mu. RELATED: 8hva (repaint_history_tail double-draw — fixed; this is the same family, opposite direction), k0ca.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-06-05T22:09:18.247154186Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-07T04:08:50.778332541Z","source_repo":"mu","source_repo_path":"<mu-checkout>","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":155,"issue_id":"mu-solo-zellij-blank-band-ptvm","author":"tcovert","text":"MITIGATION PRECEDENT (operator-found, 2026-06-05): jellyfin-tui patch (matteo-pacini/nixos-configs c8ab80b7) hit the same wall — 'zellij's Kitty/Sixel passthrough is unreliable' (re-emits/drops out-of-band sequences causing flicker) — and fixed it by detecting the ZELLIJ env var and unconditionally degrading to a conservative rendering path (halfblocks), skipping protocol probes entirely. If the bare-kitty bisect exonerates our escape emission, the same shape applies here: when ZELLIJ is set, switch insert_before to a conservative strategy (e.g., smaller-than-viewport chunked emission, or avoid the CSI T push-down branch) while bare terminals keep the codex-rs fast path. Operator installs zellij from ports — patching zellij itself is not the preferred layer.","created_at":"2026-06-05T22:48:29Z"},{"id":189,"issue_id":"mu-solo-zellij-blank-band-ptvm","author":"tcovert","text":"SECOND OPERATOR REPORT, same night (2026-06-05, recalled 2026-06-07): qwen3 session 09610bb314102c6d — 'responses come back split apart by about 20 lines. I can enter the buffer to read it, but I usually have to read just the top half, and then exit out to read the bottom. I cannot scroll through to the bottom.' Recurred across the whole session, not a one-off. Daily-driver readability impact → bumping P2->P1.","created_at":"2026-06-07T04:08:50Z"}]}
