 {"id":"mu-sqn","title":"Update rustls-webpki to fix 3 dependabot alerts (1 high, 2 low)","description":"GitHub dependabot flagged 3 alerts on main (all rustls-webpki, transitive via reqwest → rustls):\n\n  high  GHSA-82j2-j2ch-gfr8  DoS panic on malformed CRL BIT STRING\n  low   GHSA-xgp8-3hg3-c2mh  Wildcard name constraints accepted\n  low   GHSA-965h-392x-2mh5  URI name constraints incorrectly accepted\n\nReal risk for mu: modest. We talk TLS outbound to anthropic.com / chatgpt.com / openrouter.ai (well-known services). We don't process CRLs ourselves. High-severity DoS would need a malicious server in the chain.\n\nFix: cargo update -p rustls-webpki. Test the workspace still builds + tests pass. P3 because workaround = trusted upstreams.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-05-11T20:13:50.980791794Z","created_by":"tcovert","updated_at":"2026-06-07T03:56:46.887971634Z","closed_at":"2026-06-07T03:56:46.887894392Z","close_reason":"Done via PR #208 (merged 2026-06-06): rustls-webpki floored at 0.103.13 in both Cargo.tomls, Cargo.lock pinned, all 3 advisories cleared, 0 open dependabot alerts.","source_repo":"mu","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dependencies","goal:2026-06-06:8qyy","security"],"comments":[{"id":23,"issue_id":"mu-sqn","author":"tcovert","text":"Autonomous worker investigation 2026-05-15 (cost: $1.02, 19 turns): 'cargo update -p rustls-webpki' is a no-op. Both transitively-pinned versions (0.101.7 and 0.103.13) are already at their latest semver-compatible releases. Worker emitted 'blocked' envelope (correctly — no work to do under the original premise of 'just bump').\n\nTo actually close the 3 GHSA advisories, one of the following is needed:\n1. Force-upgrade to a newer minor version of rustls-webpki (beyond semver-compatible) via direct workspace dep declaration with a higher floor (e.g., '=0.104.x'). May require corresponding rustls/reqwest bumps; could cascade.\n2. Wait for upstream reqwest/rustls to release versions that bump rustls-webpki transitively to a fixed line.\n3. If the advisories don't apply to mu's usage profile (we don't process CRLs, talk only to well-known TLS endpoints), suppress in dependabot config and document the threat-model rationale.\n\nThis bead is not closeable as 'done' until one of the three paths above lands. Leaving open with this context attached so the next pick-up has the investigation results.\n\nWorker workspace at .delegations/mu-sqn-2026-05-15 cleaned up (forgotten + removed) since there are no changes to keep. Worker rev (empty) gone from jj history.","created_at":"2026-05-15T09:37:15Z"},{"id":167,"issue_id":"mu-sqn","author":"tcovert","text":"Overnight worker (cc-personal-3366ff95, goal:2026-06-06:8qyy), 2026-06-06: TERRAIN CHECK — all 3 advisories are ALREADY CLEARED on current main. Bead is ready to CLOSE; no PR needed.\n\nEvidence (gh api repos/sahuagin/mu/dependabot/alerts):\n  - GHSA-82j2-j2ch-gfr8 (high): vulnerable \"< 0.103.13\", first_patched 0.103.13 — state=fixed\n  - GHSA-xgp8-3hg3-c2mh (low):  vulnerable \"< 0.103.12\", first_patched 0.103.12 — state=fixed\n  - GHSA-965h-392x-2mh5 (low):  vulnerable \"< 0.103.12\", first_patched 0.103.12 — state=fixed\n  ZERO open dependabot alerts across all packages (paginated select(state==open) count = 0; all 6 historical alerts state=fixed).\n\nLockfile terrain: Cargo.lock pins a single rustls-webpki 0.103.13 (Cargo.lock:2797-2798), satisfying all three fixed-version floors. The vulnerable 0.101.7 entry the 2026-05-15 worker saw is GONE from the tree (consolidated by a prior rustls/reqwest bump — i.e. the \"path 2: wait for upstream\" outcome from the 2026-05-15 comment landed organically via merged PRs). \"cargo update -p rustls-webpki\" is a no-op (\"Locking 0 packages to latest compatible versions\") — already latest semver-compatible.\n\nNo code change clears these advisories further; an empty-diff PR would be fictional work. Per overnight protocol (operator asleep)